    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I was monitoring the memory usage earlier today. Did the following:\n\nstarted AS\nloaded testmap (empty map with 10 players, each having a starting slot and three mines, no preplaced resource, all AI, with me spectating, tileset is only the LAT grass tiles of RA2 temperate to keep it within the 512 sheetsize)\nabandoned game immediately\nrestarted game\nabandoned game\nrestarted game - decided to watch this one\ngot a VRAM crash in the first minute\n\nYes, I'm still on my despised Intel HD2000, but without restarting the game I can watch 30-40 minutes without a crash (depends on action). Somewhere VRAM is getting leaked for sure. I'm willing to create a tileset package for RA2 containing the YR-Terrain Expansion tiles as well, if that helps debugging this.\n"
  },
